text: Daniel Klicnik (born 31 May 2003) is an Austrian professional footballer. He plays as a right back for 2. Liga club Liefering.Daniel Klicnik at Soccerway He played for the FC Salzburg U19 team in the UEFA Youth League during the 2021–22 season. ==Career== He started his career with FC Zeltweg and went on to FC Judenburg. From 2016 to 2018 he played for the SK Sturm Graz Academy, and from 2018 to 2021 for the Red Bull Salzburg Academy. In 2021 he moved to FC Liefering. His debut for Liefering was in October 2021, when he came in for Samuel Major in the 11th round against FC Juniors OÖ. He left Liefering in 2023. He also played for Austria under-15 and under-16 national teams. ==References== Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian footballers Category:Association football defenders Category:FC Liefering players Category:Austrian football defenders
